// scrml.dev /reference/elements/engine
//
// Flagship feature page #1 (P1 Deliverable B). Demonstrates the
// 8-section feature template from scrml-dev-mdn-style-architecture
// deep-dive §1.1.
//
// Per architecture DD §4: code examples are pre-compiled day-1
// (Option A). The traffic-light demo below is intended to be a real
// scrml file compiled separately and embedded via an iframe; for
// day-1 the worked example renders as a syntax-highlighted code block
// with a "View live demo →" link pointing at the compiled artifact.
//
// Per master-list §0.1 A1c Wave 4: engine runtime codegen is in
// flight. The compile-and-run path for the demo may need to wait on
// Wave 4 close. Until then, the syntax-highlighted block is correct
// and adopter-readable; only the live-render is deferred.

<page>

    <article class="prose prose-slate max-w-3xl">

        // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
        // Feature page header — title, since-version, spec-link
        // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

        <header class="not-prose mb-8 pb-6 border-b border-slate-200">
            <div class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-500 mb-2">
                Reference &rsaquo; Elements
            </div>
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 font-mono">
                &lt;engine&gt;
            </h1>
            <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mt-2">
                Declares a state machine — the canonical structural form
                for "UI as a fully-handled state machine."
            </p>
            <div class="flex gap-4 mt-4 text-xs">
                <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700 rounded">
                    Available since v0.3.0 Wave 1
                </span>
                <a href="https://github.com/bryanmaclee/scrmlTS/blob/main/compiler/SPEC.md#§51"
                   class="text-blue-700 hover:text-blue-900 underline">
                    SPEC §51.0 (normative)
                </a>
            </div>
        </header>

        // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
        // §2 — Syntax (bare minimum form)
        // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">
            Syntax
        </h2>

        <pre class="bg-slate-900 text-slate-100 p-4 rounded-md text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>&lt;engine for=TypeName initial=.Variant&gt;
  &lt;Variant rule=.OtherVariant /&gt;
  ...
&lt;/engine&gt;</code></pre>

        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">for=</code>
            names the discriminating enum type. Every variant of that type
            must have a corresponding state-child or the compiler fires
            <a href="/reference/errors/E-ENGINE-INCOMPLETE-COVERAGE"
               class="font-mono text-xs text-rose-700 underline">E-ENGINE-INCOMPLETE-COVERAGE</a>.
            <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">initial=</code>
            picks the starting variant. <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">rule=</code>
            on a state-child constrains the legal transitions out of that
            variant. Compile-time enforcement where statically resolvable;
            runtime otherwise.
        </p>

        // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
        // §3 — Worked example (traffic-light demo)
        // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">
            Worked example
        </h2>

        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            A three-state traffic light. One enum type, one engine, three
            state-children, one button to cycle.
        </p>

        <pre class="bg-slate-900 text-slate-100 p-4 rounded-md text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>type Light:enum = { Red, Yellow, Green }

&lt;engine for=Light initial=.Red&gt;
  &lt;Red    rule=.Green&gt;
    Stop. Wait for green.
  &lt;/Red&gt;
  &lt;Green  rule=.Yellow&gt;
    Go.
  &lt;/Green&gt;
  &lt;Yellow rule=.Red&gt;
    Slow.
  &lt;/Yellow&gt;
&lt;/engine&gt;

&lt;button onclick=Light.advance(.Green)&gt;Cycle&lt;/button&gt;</code></pre>

        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-slate-500 italic">
            Live demo deferred to A1c Wave 4 engine runtime codegen.
            Until then, this block is the canonical scrml. Compile via
            <code class="font-mono">bun scrml compile</code> against the
            current scrmlTS HEAD to verify.
        </div>

        // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
        // §4 — Semantics
        // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">
            Semantics
        </h2>

        <ul class="space-y-3 text-slate-700">
            <li>
                <strong>Singleton per declaration site.</strong> One
                <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;engine&gt;</code>
                tag &rarr; one running machine for that scope. Cross-file
                mounting is via <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;EngineName/&gt;</code>;
                the singleton remains one instance per the
                outer-times-inner invariant per SPEC §51.0.K Machine
                Cohesion footnote.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Auto-declared variable.</strong> The engine name
                (e.g., <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">Light</code>)
                becomes the engine handle. Read the current variant via
                <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">@Light</code>.
                Write via
                <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">Light.advance(.Variant)</code>.
                Override the auto-name via
                <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">var=</code>
                if it would collide.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>
                    <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">rule=</code>
                    is a contract.
                </strong>
                Compile-time when the target is statically resolvable;
                runtime otherwise. Transitions not listed fire
                <a href="/reference/errors/E-ENGINE-INVALID-TRANSITION"
                   class="font-mono text-xs text-rose-700 underline">E-ENGINE-INVALID-TRANSITION</a>.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>
                    <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">initial=</code>
                    is required at top-level engines.
                </strong>
                Omission fires
                <a href="/reference/errors/W-ENGINE-INITIAL-MISSING"
                   class="font-mono text-xs text-amber-700 underline">W-ENGINE-INITIAL-MISSING</a>.
                Engines without an initial state are usually accidents.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-6 mb-2">
            Errors this feature can fire
        </h3>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-700 font-mono">
            <li><a href="/reference/errors/E-ENGINE-VAR-DUPLICATE" class="text-rose-700 underline">E-ENGINE-VAR-DUPLICATE</a></li>
            <li><a href="/reference/errors/E-ENGINE-INVALID-TRANSITION" class="text-rose-700 underline">E-ENGINE-INVALID-TRANSITION</a></li>
            <li><a href="/reference/errors/W-ENGINE-INITIAL-MISSING" class="text-amber-700 underline">W-ENGINE-INITIAL-MISSING</a></li>
            <li><a href="/reference/errors/W-ENGINE-SELF-WRITE-DETECTED" class="text-amber-700 underline">W-ENGINE-SELF-WRITE-DETECTED</a></li>
            <li><a href="/reference/errors/E-COMPONENT-ENGINE-SCOPE" class="text-rose-700 underline">E-COMPONENT-ENGINE-SCOPE</a></li>
            <li><a href="/reference/errors/E-HISTORY-NO-INNER-ENGINE" class="text-rose-700 underline">E-HISTORY-NO-INNER-ENGINE</a></li>
            <li><a href="/reference/errors/E-INTERNAL-RULE-NOT-COMPOSITE" class="text-rose-700 underline">E-INTERNAL-RULE-NOT-COMPOSITE</a></li>
        </ul>

        // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
        // §5 — Edge cases
        // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">
            Edge cases
        </h2>

        <ul class="space-y-4 text-slate-700">
            <li>
                <strong>Self-writes are runtime no-ops.</strong>
                <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">Light.advance(.Red)</code>
                from inside <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">.Red</code>
                is silently discarded (v0.3 Option-d idempotent self-write
                semantics). NOT a <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">rule=</code>
                violation. The compiler emits
                <a href="/reference/errors/W-ENGINE-SELF-WRITE-DETECTED"
                   class="font-mono text-xs text-amber-700 underline">W-ENGINE-SELF-WRITE-DETECTED</a>
                to surface the no-op so it doesn't slip past code review.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>
                    <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;engine&gt;</code>
                    inside a component body fires
                    <a href="/reference/errors/E-COMPONENT-ENGINE-SCOPE"
                       class="font-mono text-xs text-rose-700 underline">E-COMPONENT-ENGINE-SCOPE</a>.
                </strong>
                Components are multi-instance; engines are singletons.
                They don't compose. Use a derived engine
                (<code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">derived=expr</code>)
                or pass the current variant in as a prop and let the
                component render off the read.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Temporal triggers ride on the engine surface.</strong>
                <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;onTimeout after=… to=…/&gt;</code>
                as a child of a state-child is the engine temporal surface.
                NOT a separate timer system. Per SPEC §51.0.M.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Hierarchy is composite state-children.</strong>
                Nested <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;engine&gt;</code>
                declarations inside composite state-children preserve
                singleton semantics (outer-times-inner = one running inner
                instance). The
                <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">history=true</code>
                attribute on a composite state-child enables shallow
                history restoration via the
                <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">.Variant.history</code>
                target form. Per SPEC §51.0.N.
            </li>
        </ul>

        // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
        // §6 — Related features
        // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">
            Related features
        </h2>

        <ul class="space-y-1 text-slate-700">
            <li>
                <a href="/reference/elements/match" class="text-blue-700 hover:text-blue-900 underline">
                    &lt;match for=Type&gt;
                </a> — Tier 1 sibling. Pattern matching as a block;
                same exhaustiveness check, no active rules.
                <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">bun scrml promote --match</code>
                lifts to <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;engine&gt;</code>.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="/reference/elements/onTransition" class="text-blue-700 hover:text-blue-900 underline">
                    &lt;onTransition&gt;
                </a> — effect on transition. Attributes:
                <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">from=</code>,
                <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">to=</code>,
                <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">once</code>,
                <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">if=</code>.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="/reference/elements/onTimeout" class="text-blue-700 hover:text-blue-900 underline">
                    &lt;onTimeout&gt;
                </a> — temporal trigger as a state-child child element.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="/reference/keywords/derived" class="text-blue-700 hover:text-blue-900 underline">
                    derived=expr
                </a> — derived engines. Compute the active variant from
                another engine's state.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="/reference/elements/auth" class="text-blue-700 hover:text-blue-900 underline">
                    &lt;auth role=…&gt;
                </a> — per-role visibility. Wraps engine state-children
                that should only render for specific roles.
            </li>
        </ul>

        // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
        // §7 — Availability
        // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

